						<summary>

						<p>On the north and west walls, central shrine, Mahāliṅgasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 14: 985 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. It seems to record a decision taken by the temple authorities. It refers to a particular plot of land reclaimed by Āyiravaṉ Guṇavaṉ, his elder brother and his collateral relatives.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 343.</p>						

